cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper is about using reinforcement learning to automatically learn the learning rate for stochastic gradient descent during model training. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is focused on the development of algorithms and models for machine learning. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the experiments involve training on image datasets, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of actor-critic methods from deep reinforcement learning suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
